          MODULE=knights3
         VERSION=0.6
          SOURCE=knights-$VERSION.tar.gz
SOURCE_DIRECTORY=$BUILD_DIRECTORY/knights-$VERSION
   SOURCE_URL[0]=$SFORGE_URL/knights/$SOURCE
        WEB_SITE=http://knights.sourceforge.net/
         ENTERED=20020504
         UPDATED=20030628
           SHORT=" Knights is a graphical chess interface written for the K Desktop Environment."
cat << EOF
Knights is a graphical chess interface written for the K Desktop Environment. It's designed to be both friendly to new chess players and functional for Grand Masters. Here is a quick list of features that Knights currently has:

* Four modes of play:
      o Solitaire Chess
      o Play vs. Computer Opponents
      o Play on an Internet Chess Server
      o Computer vs. Computer
* "Preview" potential moves. ( Great for novices who don't yet know how the 
   pieces move. )
* Browse and review games you've saved or are currently playing.
* Load and Save games using Portable Game Notation (PGN).
* Customize your chessboard with Themes. 
EOF
